   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWELVE THE SPIRIT'S WORK ON AND IN</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE BELIEVERS 4 THE HOLDING LINE IN THE CARRYING OUT</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>OF THE DIVINE ECONOMY Scripture Reading: Eph 1:14; 4:30; 1 Pet 1:2; Luke 15:8-10, 17-21; Heb 13:12; 2 Cor 5:17; John 1:12-13; Rom 12:2b; Eph 4:23; Gal 6:15; 2 Cor 4:16; 1 Cor 3:12; 2 Cor 3:18; Phil 3:21; Rom 8:23 OUTLINE The divine sanctification is the holding line in the carrying out of the divine economy: Holding all of our spiritual experiences from our repentance to our glorification.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Going through our regeneration, renewing, transformation, and conformation unto the redemption of our body Eph 1:14; 4:30.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To sonize us divinely, making us sons of God that we may become the same as God in His life and in His nature but not in His Godhead , so that we may be God's expression.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Hence, God's sanctification is the divine sonizing.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The steps of the divine sanctification: The seeking sanctification the initial sanctification 1 Pet 1:2: Unto repentance Luke 15:8-10.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To bring us back to God Luke 15:17-21.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The redeeming sanctification the positional sanctification: By the blood of Christ Heb 13:12.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To transfer us from Adam to Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The regenerating sanctification the beginning of the dispositional sanctification: Renewing us from our spirit 2 Cor 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To make us, the sinners, sons of God John 1:12-13.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The renewing sanctification the continuation of the dispositional sanctification: Renewing our soul from our mind through all the parts of our soul Rom 12:2b; Eph 4:23.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To make our soul a part of God's new creation Gal 6:15.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The transforming sanctification the daily sanctification 2 Cor 4:16: Reconstituting us with the element of Christ metabolically.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To make us a new constitution as a part of the organic Body of Christ 1 Cor 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The conforming sanctification the shaping sanctification: Shaping us in the image of the glorious Christ 2 Cor 3:18.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To make us the expression of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The glorifying sanctification the consummating sanctification: Redeeming our body by transfiguring it Phil 3:21.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>To make us Christ's expression in full in glory Rom 8:23.</S>
   </TEXT>
